      section.s5
        ul
          li.l2 Playing Tic Tac Toe on a 3x3 Board
          li 1. X always goes first.
          li 2. Players alternate placing Xs and Os on the board until either (a) one player has three in a row, horizontally, vertically or diagonally; or (b) all nine squares are filled.
          li 3. If a player is able to draw three Xs or three Os in a row, that player wins.
          li 4. If all nine squares are filled and neither player has three in a row, the game is a draw.
          li
